# Command gitme

## What does this command do:

Easily find local Git repos

## Installed from

Forked from https://github.com/davorg/gitme — using https://github.com/kevinpinscoe/gitme

For Fedora install using: `git clone git@github.com:kevinpinscoe/gitme.git ~/bin/gitme`
For Raspberry Pi install using: `git clone git@github.com:kevinpinscoe/gitme.git ~/bin/gitme`
For Mac install using: `git clone git@github.com:kevinpinscoe/gitme.git ~/bin/gitme`

## Command path

Sourced automatically at shell startup via `~/.bash.d/30_bash_autocomplete` (bash) and `30_zsh_autocomplete` (zsh). Run `reload` after first clone to activate without opening a new shell.

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/kevinpinscoe/gitme

## Ignore file

Create `~/.gitme/ignore` to exclude repos from search results at runtime.
Each line is a bash glob matched against the full repo path.
Lines starting with # are comments. No cache rebuild needed after editing.

# Exclude all repos under a directory
/home/kinscoe/Projects/3rd-party-repos/*

# Exclude a specific repo
/home/kinscoe/bin/gitme

Override the ignore file path: `export GITME_IGNORE=/path/to/ignore-file`

## Command options

# Jump to a repo by name or partial name
gitme <search-term>

# Jump to a repo matching a remote URL or fragment
gitme github.com/kevinpinscoe

# Rebuild the repository cache (faster searching)
gitme --rebuild-cache

# Show help
gitme --help

# Show version
gitme --version
